What's New with Woo

In 2025, evolution is the name of the game. We're building a more powerful, future-proof WooCommerce - with feedback from developers like you shaping our work at every step.

Take a look at our 2025 roadmap for a preview of what's in store - from stronger high-volume support and commerce-first modernizations to a major expansion of our core capabilities.

See what's next

New in our Marketplace

Enable last-click analytics
Help clients learn more about what customers like (and where to focus next) with advanced order attribution reporting in WooCommerce Analytics.
At a glance, stores can discover which campaigns, channels, and traffic sources are driving sales - and make data-driven decisions to get the most out of their marketing.
Dive into the details
Dive into the details

Set up full catalog control
Make sure clients have complete control of their product catalog with this extensive customization tool.
Seamlessly manage product visibility, pricing displays, add-to-cart and checkout options, and much more, so stores always look and operate exactly as planned.
Customize the experience
Customize the experience

New in WooCommerce 9.6
  • WooCommerce Brands is now part of our core platform and enabled for all users. Create dedicated brand pages, add brand details to product pages, and improve navigation with brand-specific search - see how it works.
  • We now match the default weight and dimension units to a store's location during onboarding - and units will automatically update when the location is changed.
  • The Product Summary block has gotten a huge revamp with text styling updates, a removable word count limit, and more custom controls.

Bite-sized updates
  • Ready to dive into WooCommerce development? Check out Ján's guide to setting up your dev environment, working with the monorepo, and making awesome contributions.
  • Feedback wanted! As we work to integrate order fulfillment into WooCommerce core, let us know how it can best serve you.
